The paper deals with quantitative games, which are a topic in both logic (cs.LO) and game theory (cs.GT). The introduction of a new technique for solving such games is likely to be of interest to researchers in both fields. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of vertex-ranked games, which are a type of infinite game that can be analyzed using techniques from both computer science (cs.DS, cs.AI) and logic (cs.PL).
